147040.name: butterfly_population
147040.description: Population data measures the number of butterflies counted at fixed measuring points in the Netherlands. This is presented as an index across 50 tracked butterfly species.
147040.datasetName: Butterfly population and distribution in Netherlands

source.name: CBS, PBL, RIVM, WUR (2021). Central Bureau of Statistics (CBS); PBL Netherlands Environmental Assessment Agency.
source.dataPublishedBy: CBS, PBL, RIVM, WUR (2021). Trend of butterflies, 1992-2020 (indicator 1386, version 18 , June 7, 2021 ). www.clo.nl. Central Bureau of Statistics (CBS), The Hague; PBL Netherlands Environmental Assessment Agency, The Hague; RIVM National Institute for Public Health and the Environment, Bilthoven; and Wageningen University and Research, Wageningen.
source.additionalInfo:
Population data measures the number of butterflies counted at fixed measuring points in the Netherlands. This is presented as an index across 50 tracked butterfly species.

Distribution data measures the number of square kilometers occupied by butterflies. This is presented as an index across 49 tracked butterfly species.
